oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Homes Near Lake Street in East Nashville Urban Renewal Area, c.1950s
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph of homes near Lake Street in the East Nashville Urban Renewal area, circa late-1950s. The East Nashville Urban Renewal Project was the largest urban renewal project in the U.S. in the late-1950s. The project area comprised 2,256 acres of reclaimed city property, containing 5,570 structures with 8,617 dwelling units, and it anticipated approximately $21,000,000 in capital improvements. Photographed by the Nashville Housing Authority. Forms part of the MDHA Photograph Collection. 1 photograph : b & w.
